  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "To prevent `prysm` from highjacking port 8080, which is already used by our application server, I temporarily want to disable the prysm metrics via:\r\n```\r\n... --monitoring-port -1\r\n```\r\nHowever, prysm gives a rather ugly error on this:\r\n```\r\nlevel=error msg=\"Could not listen to host:port :127.0.0.1:-1\" error=\"listen tcp: address -1: invalid port\" prefix=prometheus\r\n```\r\nWould be nicer if prysm would say on `--monitoring-port -1` something like: disabling monitoring service, really dude?",
